    "SUMMARY": "CS Gloria 2018 Bistrița-Năsăud, commonly known as Gloria Bistrița, is a professional women's handball club in Bistrița, Bistrița-Năsăud, Romania, that competes in the Liga Naţională.\nGloria Bistrița firstly reached the quarterfinals of the EHF European League in 2020 when they were eventually knocked out by Ikast Håndbold.\nSecond time the team reached the quarterfinals of the EHF European League  in  2024."
